Movie: The Private Life of Sherlock Holmes
Review: Impressively unbalanced portrayal of the OG dynamic detective duo. Skirts around some moments of real pathos—Wilder's hesitancy to commit is a detriment to the film, though Stephens is delightful to watch throughout. No wonder every Holmes entry since Wilder's has wanted to borrow some of this. Moffat could never.
